Check out this #PROtip from @erik.wella to get the inside scoop on highlighting curly hair:

"I love using a herringbone sectioning to create a lot of dimension (shown on the mannequin head) and the results shown my super cute model!"

#Protip - when highlighting curly hair, I typically use a larger weave and alternate with slicing. Curly hair tends to look darker when it’s dry and in natural form. So a more impactful placement is necessary. 

#PROformula:
A. Lift: Highlights: Blondorplex + 6 vol
B. Root Shadow: 6/19 + 7/ + 6 vol Illumina Color
C. Tone A: 7/31 + 6 vol 
  Tone B: 8/13 + 6 vol
Alternating toning formulas A and B on every other section #wellahair #wellalife #wellaeducation #stylistspotlight @wellahairusa
